Reflections

By the lakeside, 
I sit in quiet, 
holding my breath, 
watching the world unfold, 

the waters mirror tales,
branches sway, 
singing hymns of time.

Each ripple a reminder, 
every glance a blessing, 
in nature’s embrace, 
I find my place.

- Nikki Giovanni
